title: Lais Ribeiro and Myla Dalbesio Sports Illustrated Rookies
text:
Myla Dalbesio and Lais Ribeiro were named as two of the newest members of the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit's 2017 Rookie Class on Tuesday.
Lovely photos of the models in skimpy bikinis while in warm-weather locales were shared when the announcement was made.
They follow looker Kelly Gale who was named as a Rookie the day before.
New face for SI: Myla Dalbesio was named one of the newest members of the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit's 2017 Rookie Class on Tuesday
Mayla wore blue bikini bottoms as she lay tummy down on a beach. It appeared as if she was topless, but there was a string along her back indicating she may have had a nude-colored bikini top on.
Myla was raised in Racine, Wisconsin.
Her modeling career began after she won Miss Teen Wisconsin at age 16. With her appreciation for the human form, Myla doesn’t just enjoy being in front of a camera, she also likes to be behind the camera, as seen in her self-photographed spread for the first non-nude issue of Playboy.
Another stunner: Lais Ribeiro was also named. Laisa had on a reddish brown string bikini as she leaded against a rock. Behind her were an array of waterfalls
Laisa had on a reddish brown string bikini as she leaded against a rock. Behind her were an array of waterfalls.
A native, of rural Miguel Alves, Brazil, Lais began modeling in 2009.
She made her modeling debut in the Brazilian version of ELLE, before moving to New York City in 2010. Lais’s curvaceous figure fueled her rise to the top of the New York fashion scene by walking the runway for top designers—Marc Jacobs, Vera Wang, Michael Kors, Roberto Cavalli and Dolce & Gabanna, to name a few—but it was her first appearance at the VS Fashion Show which cemented her status as one of the world’s top models.
Big break: On the rise model Kelly Gale was the first looker to be named as Sports Illustrated Swimsuit 2017 Rookie Class
On Monday Kelly, 21, was the first model to be named as one of the members of Sports Illustrated Swimsuit's 2017 Rookie Class.
The Indian-Australian fashion model, originally from Sweden, looked sensational in a printed colourful bikini as she posed laying on the beach for the publication.
Nice life! She posted a photo last week with the caption: 'Beach days are the best days, except spa days at the beach, those are even better'
Aside from her bikini, she merely accessorized with a simple chain necklace as she went for a natural but smouldering make-up look.
Her skin looked flawless and radiant, as she opted to wear a little foundation and some pink blush.
She added natural pink lipstick and a little bit of smokey eye make-up to complete her beach chic look.

In demand: The 5′ 10″ model has also walked the runway for the annual Victoria Secret Fashion Show in 2013, 2014 and 2016
The 5′ 10″ model has also walked the runway for the annual Victoria Secret Fashion Show in 2013, 2014 and 2016.
The brunette beauty has had a lot of practice posing on the beach as she regularly uploads photos on Instagram of her decked out in bikinis.
She posted a photo last week with the caption: 'Beach days are the best days, except spa days at the beach, those are even better.'
She simply wore a white towel as she showed off her flawless décolletage and smooth skin.

She also posted a photo recently of her in a bright red bikini as she lounged on a bed reading a book.
Kelly, along with other SI models, will be at the VIBES Sports Illustrated Swimsuit festival in Houston in a few weeks.
The two-day event starts February 17 with a food festival and a performance by R&B sensation Miguel.
Grammy Award-winning producer DJ Diplo will also be headlining at the event.
